FBIS3-47622 "dreas010_d_94005" FBIS-EAS-94-010 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Jan 1994 South Korea First 21st Century Committee Meeting With U.S. Set SK1401062894 Seoul YONHAP in English 0617 GMT 14 Jan 94 SK1401062894 Seoul YONHAP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Seoul, Jan. 14 (YONHAP) -- The 21st Century Committee, created by South Korea and the United States, will hold its first meeting next month in Washington, the Foreign Ministry said Friday. For three days, Feb. 17-19, prominent politicians, economists, scholars and businessmen, including U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher, will discuss how to expand cooperation and will present reports and recommendations on improving relations. Sakong Il, a former finance minister, and Fred Bergsten, a former deputy Treasury secretary, led preparations to form the committee.
